      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 47
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "Offering a mechanically sorted 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, featuring the iconic 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. This example maintains strong compression across all rotors and exhibits a seamless transition between the primary and secondary Hitachi HT12 turbochargers at the 4,500 RPM crossover point. The chassis remains true to its 50/50 weight distribution, supported by a factory-spec aluminum double-wishbone suspension and a responsive Torsen limited-slip differential. Recent preventative maintenance includes a full cooling system refresh with an upgraded aluminum radiator to mitigate heat soak and a comprehensive vacuum line simplification for improved actuator reliability. The 5-speed manual transmission shifts crisply with no synchro grind. This is a high-performance, analog machine tuned for the purist who values kinetic feedback and rotary precision.",
